## 4. BACKEND — JAVA 17 + SPRING BOOT 3.2.5

### Naming
- Classes: `PascalCase` | Methods & variables: `camelCase` | Constants: `ALL_CAPS` | Packages: `lowercase`

### Service pattern (mandatory)
```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Transactional
public class XyzServiceImpl implements XyzService {

    private final XyzRepository xyzRepository;

    @Override
    @Transactional(readOnly = true)
    public XyzResponse getById(UUID id) {
        Xyz entity = xyzRepository.findById(id)
                .orElseThrow(() -> new NotFoundException("Xyz not found"));
        return mapToResponse(entity);
    }

    private XyzResponse mapToResponse(Xyz e) {
        return new XyzResponse(e.getId(), e.getName(), e.getCreatedAt());
    }
}
```

### Exception pattern — use only these
```java
throw new BadRequestException("message");        // 400
throw new NotFoundException("Entity not found"); // 404
throw new UnauthorizedException("message");      // 401
```

### DTO — Java records only
```java
public record XyzResponse(UUID id, String name, Instant createdAt) {}
public record CreateXyzRequest(@NotBlank String name, @NotNull @Positive BigDecimal price) {}
```

### Controller pattern
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/xyz")
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class XyzController {
    private final XyzService xyzService;

    @GetMapping("/{id}")
    public ResponseEntity<XyzResponse> getById(@PathVariable UUID id) {
        return ResponseEntity.ok(xyzService.getById(id));
    }

    @PostMapping
    public ResponseEntity<XyzResponse> create(
            @AuthenticationPrincipal String userId,
            @Valid @RequestBody CreateXyzRequest request) {
        return ResponseEntity.ok(xyzService.create(request, UUID.fromString(userId)));
    }
}
```

### Token generation — SecureRandom mandatory
```java
// ✅ CORRECT
byte[] bytes = new byte[64];
new SecureRandom().nextBytes(bytes);
String token = Base64.getUrlEncoder().withoutPadding().encodeToString(bytes);

// ❌ WRONG
UUID.randomUUID().toString();
```

### Avoid N+1 queries
```java
// ❌ BAD
products.stream().map(p -> {
    List<Review> reviews = reviewRepository.findByProductId(p.getId()); // N queries!
    return mapToResponse(p, reviews);
});

// ✅ GOOD
@Query("SELECT p FROM Product p LEFT JOIN FETCH p.reviews WHERE p.status = :status")
List<Product> findByStatusWithReviews(@Param("status") ProductStatus status);
```

- **EduCycle:** `ProductServiceImpl.mapAllWithReviews` dùng batch `ReviewRepository.findByProductIdIn` (không gọi `findByProductId` trong vòng lặp).

### Logging — @Slf4j
```java
log.info("Product created: {} by user {}", product.getId(), userId);  // business events
log.warn("OTP expired for transaction {}", transactionId);             // recoverable
log.error("Unexpected error", exception);                              // system failure
```

### RESTful conventions
- `GET` list/get · `POST` create → 200/201 · `PUT` full update · `PATCH` partial/action · `DELETE` → 204

