## 5. FRONTEND — REACT 19 + VITE 7 (JavaScript)

### Status — always normalize to UPPERCASE
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT
transaction.status?.toUpperCase() === 'PENDING'
user?.role?.toUpperCase() === 'ADMIN'
['COMPLETED', 'REJECTED'].includes(status?.toUpperCase())

// ❌ WRONG — backend sends UPPERCASE, these never match
transaction.status === 'Pending'
user?.role === 'Admin'
```

### CSS — design tokens only
```css
/* ✅ */ color: var(--primary-500);  padding: var(--space-4);
/* ❌ */ color: #2196f3;             padding: 16px;
```

### Code style
```javascript
const handleSubmit = async (e) => {            // const arrow + handle prefix
  e.preventDefault();
  if (!email) return toast.error('...');       // early return
  // happy path
};
```

### API calls
```javascript
import { authApi, productsApi, transactionsApi, messagesApi,
         reviewsApi, notificationsApi, categoriesApi, adminApi, aiApi } from '../api/endpoints';

const res = await productsApi.getById(id);     // call
return res.data;                               // use

const msg = err.response?.data?.message || err.response?.data || 'Lỗi không xác định'; // error
// Hoặc err.userFacingMessage từ interceptor (`getApiErrorMessage` trong `apiError.js`)
```

### Contexts
```javascript
const { user, token, isAuthenticated, isAdmin,
        login, register, logout, updateProfile,
        verifyOtp, resendOtp, socialLogin, verifyPhone } = useAuth();

const { notifications, unreadCount, markAsRead, markAllAsRead, fetchRecent } = useNotifications();
